title: Welcome To React Tutorial Part 1
details: You learned from the previous chapter that Bootstrap requires a containing element to wrap site contents. Containers are used to pad the content inside of them, and there are two container classes available: 1.The .container class provides a responsive fixed width container 2.The .container-fluid class provides a full width container, spanning the entire width of the viewport
